Explain How Does API Document arranged

The API Document have pages which correspond to things in navigation_bar, Show as below.

  • Totalview

    the Totalview Page hold Front-Page for this API ALSO Provided List of All Packages with conclusion for each. In addition, page also hold an Total details for all Set-packages.

  • PACKAGES

    Every Package have page which holds List for all classes AND Interfaces, with a conclusion of each. This given page holds 6-Categories:

    • interfaces (italic)
    • classes
    • e_nums
    • exceptions
    • errors
    • annotation_Types

  • class/interface

    Every class, Interface, nesting-class and interface have its Own Separated-pages. Every This pages have 3-part Consisting for a Class or Interface details, Conclusion -tables, and fact Member details:

    • class Inheritance Figure
    • Direct-Sub_Classe
    • All Given Sub_interfaces
    • All Given Implementing Classes
    • class/Interface details
    • class/Interface details
    • Nesting-class Conclusion
    • Domain Conclusion
    • Construction Conclusion
    • Methods Conclusion
    • Domain Facts
    • Constructions Facts
    • Method Facts

    Every Conclusion Entry hold 1-sentence from facts Description of given items. The Conclusion Entries is in Alphabetical-order, although facts Description is in the order It will show into Sourc- Code. This extracts the Logical-classifications installed by the Programmer.

  • annotation-type

    Every annotation Types have its own separating Pages with Previous Section:

    • annotation-type Declaration
    • annotation -type description
    • require-factor conclusion
    • optional-factor conclusion
    • Factor Facts

  • e_num

    Every e_num have its own separating Pages with Previous Section:

    • e_num declare
    • e_num facts
    • e_num Constant_Conclusion
    • e_num Constant_Facts

  • Use_ability

    Every document-Packages, Classes AND Interfaces have its own Use_ability Pages. These pages show which Packages, Classes, Methods, Constructors and Fields using Any_part of the provided classes Or Package. Already given a Class or Interface a, it Used page attached Sub_classes of a, Fields Declared as a, Methods which Return a AND Methods AND Constructors With Parameter Of the type a.You are able to Access the page through First go into the package, Class OR Interface, and after that click on the "Use" link in Navigation-Bar.

  • TrEE (class-hierarchy)

    Inside the class-hierarchy Page of all Packages, also a Hierarchy Of Each Package. each Hierarchy Page holds list of Classes AND list of Interface. The Classes are arranged By Inheritance Structure Start With java.lang.Object. the Interfaces don't Inherit From java.lang.Object.

    • During view Totalview Page, click At "Tree" show Hierarchy of All Packages.
    • During view a Particular Package, Class or Interface Page, click "Tree" show Hierarchy for Only That given package.

  • Deprecated API

    The Deprecated API Page Lists All Of The API That has been Deprecated. A deprecated API isn't mentioned for Use, Generally as things go Improvement, AND a replace API is commonly Given. Deprecated APIs may be Remove In-future Implementations.

  • InD

    The InD holds an Alphabetic List of All Classes, Interfaces, Constructors, Methods AND Fields.

  • Previous/Following

    Inside the Links will Take you To Following or Previous Class, Interface, Package, or Related-Page.

  • FFrAmE/No FrAmE

    Inside the Links Show AND Hide HTML FrAmE. All Pages are obtainable With OR Without Frames.

  • all-classes

    The all-classes link Show all Classes AND Interfaces Except the Non-Static Nesting Types.

  • serialized-form

    Every Serializable OR Externalizable Class have details of its Serialization Fields AND Methods. This Information is of Interest to Re-Implementors, Not To Developer Use API. although there isn't link in the Navigation-Bar, we could get To This Information By Going To Any Serialize Class and Click on "Serialized Form" In "See also" Section Of Class details.

  • Constant-Domain values

    The Constant-Domain values The Page List Static Final domains and their Corresponding Values.

This will Help File Applies to API-Documentation Created Using Standard doc_let.
